---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<BaseHead title={`Security Compliance - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Understanding New Zealand security frameworks including NZISM and Protective Security Requirements for organizational security planning." />

<Header />
<main>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Security Compliance Guidance</h1>
			<p class="tagline">Understanding New Zealand's Security Framework Requirements</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="compliance-content">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="intro">
				<p>Navigating New Zealand's security compliance landscape requires understanding key government frameworks. We help organizations comprehend these requirements and identify appropriate security solutions.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="framework-overview">
				<h2>Understanding Key Security Frameworks</h2>
				
				<div class="framework-item">
					<h3>NZISM (New Zealand Information Security Manual)</h3>
					<p>The government's comprehensive manual for protecting official information. It outlines security controls, risk management approaches, and technical requirements for government agencies and their partners.</p>
					<div class="our-role">
						<strong>Our Approach:</strong> We help interpret NZISM requirements and identify commercial solutions that align with its security objectives.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="framework-item">
					<h3>Protective Security Requirements (PSR)</h3>
					<p>An all-of-government framework covering personnel, physical, and information security measures for protecting sensitive government information.</p>
					<div class="our-role">
						<strong>Our Approach:</strong> We provide guidance on PSR alignment and recommend security practices that support compliance objectives.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="framework-item">
					<h3>International Security Standards</h3>
					<p>Various international standards and certifications recognized within New Zealand security frameworks, including FIPS 140-2, Common Criteria, and other validation programs.</p>
					<div class="our-role">
						<strong>Our Approach:</strong> We help identify products with relevant certifications that may support your security and compliance goals.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="capabilities">
				<h2>How We Can Assist</h2>
				<div class="capability-grid">
					<div class="capability">
						<h3>Framework Education</h3>
						<p>Helping your team understand NZISM, PSR, and other relevant security requirements and how they apply to your organization.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="capability">
						<h3>Solution Identification</h3>
						<p>Recommending commercially available security products and solutions that align with framework requirements.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="capability">
						<h3>Implementation Support</h3>
						<p>Assisting with the deployment and configuration of security solutions in your environment.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="disclaimer-box">
				<h3>Important Information</h3>
				<p><strong>Hermetrix Technologies provides advisory services and implementation support for security solutions.</strong> We are not a government agency and cannot provide official compliance certifications or security clearances.</p>
				<p>Formal compliance status, security accreditations, and government approvals must be obtained through the appropriate official channels. We support your journey toward compliance through education and appropriate solution implementation.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="cta-section">
				<h2>Need to Understand Compliance Requirements?</h2>
				<p>Contact us to discuss how we can help your organization navigate security framework requirements.</p>
				<div class="contact-methods">
					<a href="mailto:hello@hermetrix.nz" class="btn primary">General Inquiry</a>
					<a href="mailto:security@hermetrix.nz" class="btn secondary">Framework Consultation</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</main>
<Footer />

<style>
body {
	margin: 0;
	min-height: 100vh;
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
	font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
	line-height: 1.6;
}

main {
	flex: 1;
}

	/* Hero Section */
	.hero {
	padding: 4rem 2rem;
	text-align: center;
	background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f1419 0%, #1a365d 50%, #2d3748 100%);
	color: white;
	position: relative;
	overflow: hidden;
}
.hero::before {
	content: "";
	position: absolute;
	top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
	background: url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg width="100%25" height="100%25" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><circle fill="%2363b3ed" fill-opacity="0.05" cx="10%25" cy="20%25" r="80"/><circle fill="%2363b3ed" fill-opacity="0.03" cx="80%25" cy="70%25" r="120"/><circle fill="%2390cdf4" fill-opacity="0.04" cx="50%25" cy="50%25" r="100"/></svg>');
	z-index: 0;
}
.hero > .container {
	position: relative;
	z-index: 1;
	}

	.hero h1 {
					font-size: 4rem;
					margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
					font-family: 'Montserrat', 'Segoe UI', 'Arial Black', Arial, sans-serif;
					font-weight: 900;
					color: #ffffff;
					text-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3), 0 2px 0 #1a365d;
					letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	.tagline {
		font-size: 1.8rem;
		font-weight: 400;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		color: #90cdf4;
	}

	.compliance-content {
		padding: 4rem 1rem;
		background: #f8fafc;
	}

	.intro {
		text-align: center;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.framework-overview {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 4rem;
	}

	.framework-overview h2 {
		color: #1a365d;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 2rem;
	}

	.framework-item {
		background: #f8fafc;
		padding: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		border-left: 4px solid #1a365d;
	}

	.framework-item h3 {
		color: #1a365d;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-size: 1.3rem;
	}

	.our-role {
		background: #e6fffa;
		border-left: 4px solid #38b2ac;
		padding: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}

	.capabilities {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
	}

	.capabilities h2 {
					text-align: center;
					margin-bottom: 3rem;
					font-size: 3rem;
					color: #0f1419;
					font-family: 'Montserrat', 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
					font-weight: 700;
					letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	}

	.capability-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
	}

	.capability {
		background: white;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.capability h3 {
		color: #1a365d;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}

	.disclaimer-box {
		background: #fffaf0;
		border: 1px solid #fed7aa;
		border-left: 4px solid #ed8936;
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		margin: 3rem auto;
		max-width: 800px;
	}

	.disclaimer-box h3 {
		color: #c05621;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.disclaimer-box p {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.cta-section {
		text-align: center;
		padding: 3rem 2rem;
		background: #1a365d;
		color: white;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.cta-section h2 {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		color: #90cdf4;
		font-size: 2.2rem;
		font-family: 'Montserrat', 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	}

	.contact-methods {
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
		margin: 0 0.5rem;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-radius: 0.375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		transition: all 0.2s;
	}

	.btn.primary {
		background-color: #90cdf4;
		color: #1a365d;
	}

	.btn.primary:hover {
		background-color: #63b3ed;
	}

	.btn.secondary {
		background-color: transparent;
		color: #90cdf4;
		border: 2px solid #90cdf4;
	}

	.btn.secondary:hover {
		background-color: #90cdf4;
		color: #1a365d;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	/* Mobile responsiveness */
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.contact-methods {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 1rem;
		}
		
		.btn {
			margin: 0;
		}
	}
</style>
